1
00:00:00,767 --> 00:00:01,467
<i>michael:
my name is michael westen.</i>

2
00:00:02,334 --> 00:00:03,367
<i>i used to be a spy until...</i>

3
00:00:03,434 --> 00:00:04,834
[ cellphone rings ]

4
00:00:04,901 --> 00:00:07,501
Man: we got a burn notice
on you. you're blacklisted.

5
00:00:07,567 --> 00:00:09,934
<i>when you're burned,
you've got nothing --</i>

6
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:12,601
<i>no cash, no credit,
no job history.</i>

7
00:00:12,667 --> 00:00:15,000
<i>you're stuck in whatever city
they decide to dump you in.</i>

8
00:00:15,067 --> 00:00:17,033
Where am i?
miami.

9
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:20,267
<i>you do whatever work
comes your way.</i>

10
00:00:20,334 --> 00:00:22,901
<i>you rely on anyone
who's still talking to you.</i>

11
00:00:22,968 --> 00:00:24,534
<i>a trigger-happy
ex-girlfriend...</i>

12
00:00:24,601 --> 00:00:26,167
Should we shoot them?

13
00:00:26,234 --> 00:00:28,734
<i>...an old friend who used
to inform on you to the fbi...</i>

14
00:00:28,801 --> 00:00:31,100
You know spies --
a bunch of bitchy little girls.

15
00:00:31,167 --> 00:00:33,601
<i>...family, too...
hey, is that your mom again?</i>

16
00:00:33,667 --> 00:00:35,801
<i>...if you're desperate.
someone needs your help,
michael.</i>

17
00:00:35,868 --> 00:00:38,300
<i>bottom line --
as long as you're burned,</i>

18
00:00:38,367 --> 00:00:39,968
<i>you're not going anywhere.</i>

19
00:00:54,534 --> 00:00:55,968
[ knock on door ]

20
00:00:56,033 --> 00:00:57,367
Man: open up! police!

21
00:00:57,434 --> 00:00:58,767
<i>whether you're dealing</i>

22
00:00:58,834 --> 00:01:00,234
<i>with the presidential guard
in belarus,</i>

23
00:01:00,300 --> 00:01:02,067
<i>the federal security service
in russia,</i>

24
00:01:02,133 --> 00:01:03,534
<i>or the local police in miami,</i>

25
00:01:03,601 --> 00:01:05,434
<i>the drill is
pretty much the same --</i>

26
00:01:05,501 --> 00:01:07,968
<i>keep your place clean
of damning evidence.</i>

27
00:01:08,033 --> 00:01:11,100
<i>keep your alibis
and your whereabouts straight,</i>

28
00:01:11,167 --> 00:01:13,567
<i>and always be ready
for surprise visits.</i>

29
00:01:16,701 --> 00:01:18,501
Nate.
what are you doing here?

30
00:01:18,567 --> 00:01:21,300
Just giving you a little
taste of what i woke up
to this morning, bro.

31
00:01:21,367 --> 00:01:22,968
I was dragged out of bed

32
00:01:23,033 --> 00:01:24,901
By someone very interested
in you.

33
00:01:26,467 --> 00:01:28,801
Mr. westen.
you mind if i come in?

34
00:01:31,133 --> 00:01:33,534
By all means.

35
00:01:33,601 --> 00:01:35,901
You know, if these visits
become a habit,

36
00:01:35,968 --> 00:01:38,133
I'm gonna start thinking
you like me.

37
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:40,734
Oh, you remember my partner,
detective lopez.

38
00:01:40,801 --> 00:01:42,467
I'm not sure
you two formally met.

39
00:01:45,367 --> 00:01:47,000
I'm glad you're here.

40
00:01:47,067 --> 00:01:49,767
I got a gift for you.
my daily activity log.

41
00:01:49,834 --> 00:01:51,000
Hmm.

42
00:01:51,067 --> 00:01:53,367
We were just
dropping nate off.

43
00:01:53,434 --> 00:01:54,567
Just a way to say thank you

44
00:01:54,634 --> 00:01:56,167
For chatting to us
about his big brother.

45
00:01:56,234 --> 00:01:58,133
And i thought it wouldn't hurt
to see if you were free today

46
00:01:58,200 --> 00:01:59,434
To answer some questions.

47
00:01:59,501 --> 00:02:00,601
I'm crazy busy.

48
00:02:00,667 --> 00:02:01,801
I need to finish my yogurt.

49
00:02:01,868 --> 00:02:02,934
Then i was planning
on working out.

50
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:05,968
Well, until your calendar
clears up,

51
00:02:06,033 --> 00:02:07,868
Just know
i'm gonna make my way

52
00:02:07,934 --> 00:02:11,067
Through every friend, relative,
and associate you have.

53
00:02:11,133 --> 00:02:12,734
Let me save you some time.

54
00:02:12,801 --> 00:02:15,300
My friends and family
don't know anything.

55
00:02:15,367 --> 00:02:17,200
Sooner or later,
someone will.

56
00:02:17,267 --> 00:02:18,767
When you want this to stop.

57
00:02:24,734 --> 00:02:27,200
How long you been
in town?

58
00:02:27,267 --> 00:02:28,734
About six hours,

59
00:02:28,801 --> 00:02:30,033
Five of which were spent

60
00:02:30,100 --> 00:02:31,801
Listening to your girlfriend
over there tell me

61
00:02:31,868 --> 00:02:32,934
That i'd fled to vegas

62
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:34,534
To avoid
some unpaid parking tickets.

63
00:02:34,601 --> 00:02:36,133
She was just trying
to soften you up,

64
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:37,434
Trying to get you
to flip on me.

65
00:02:37,501 --> 00:02:38,567
Yeah.

66
00:02:38,634 --> 00:02:40,133
I figured that out
after she said

67
00:02:40,200 --> 00:02:42,033
It would go easier
if i flipped on my brother.

68
00:02:43,701 --> 00:02:45,434
Jesus, bro, i didn't say
anything, all right?

69
00:02:45,501 --> 00:02:47,000
But do you know
how hard it is

70
00:02:47,067 --> 00:02:49,100
Not to talk about your
extracurricular activities?

71
00:02:49,167 --> 00:02:50,267
[ sighs ]

72
00:02:50,334 --> 00:02:51,701
All right.
drive me to mom's.

73
00:02:51,767 --> 00:02:53,367
My car is there.
i need to get to my meeting.

74
00:02:53,434 --> 00:02:54,467
Meeting?

75
00:02:54,534 --> 00:02:55,901
Limos, bro.

76
00:02:55,968 --> 00:02:57,734
I came back
to talk with investors

77
00:02:57,801 --> 00:02:59,133
About expanding my company.

78
00:03:00,601 --> 00:03:02,200
This is real.
okay?

79
00:03:02,267 --> 00:03:04,501
Things are finally
breaking my way.

80
00:03:04,567 --> 00:03:05,534
Help me out?

81
00:03:21,067 --> 00:03:22,701
So, nate didn't
give her anything?

82
00:03:22,767 --> 00:03:24,767
If there's one thing
nate westen knows how to do,

83
00:03:24,834 --> 00:03:25,934
It's avoid telling
the truth.

84
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:27,834
Well, that's good news
for now.

85
00:03:27,901 --> 00:03:30,534
But how long before paxson
finds someone you know

86
00:03:30,601 --> 00:03:33,400
That she can flip,
like a gun runner named seymour?

87
00:03:33,467 --> 00:03:34,934
Or a money launderer
named barry?

88
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:36,968
Or a washed-up navy seal
named sam?

89
00:03:37,067 --> 00:03:39,400
Or how about
an unstable, jealous --

90
00:03:39,467 --> 00:03:40,834
Guys.

91
00:03:40,901 --> 00:03:42,434
If paxson's going after
everyone i know,

92
00:03:42,501 --> 00:03:44,801
Then i need to get
to know someone she'll
regret going after.

93
00:03:44,868 --> 00:03:47,033
Not a bad idea.
make it look like

94
00:03:47,100 --> 00:03:48,501
You're mixed up with someone
with a little bit of clout,

95
00:03:48,567 --> 00:03:50,601
Maybe somebody
from the mayor's office.

96
00:03:50,667 --> 00:03:52,968
I'm thinking
a financial relationship,

97
00:03:53,033 --> 00:03:55,200
Something
that looks very suspicious,

98
00:03:55,267 --> 00:03:56,467
But isn't actually illegal.

99
00:03:56,534 --> 00:03:57,567
Sounds fun.

100
00:03:57,634 --> 00:03:59,033
Thanks, sam.

101
00:03:59,100 --> 00:04:02,534
<i>the lone spy who always
works solo is a myth.</i>

102
00:04:02,601 --> 00:04:05,000
<i>the truth is,
you don't last long</i>

103
00:04:05,067 --> 00:04:07,100
<i>without keeping
a few friends around,</i>

104
00:04:07,167 --> 00:04:09,501
<i>because your enemies
will find you on their own.</i>

105
00:04:09,567 --> 00:04:12,400
You wouldn't happen to know
where i could find a burned spy,

106
00:04:12,467 --> 00:04:13,434
Would you?

107
00:04:13,501 --> 00:04:15,200
Brennen.

108
00:04:18,868 --> 00:04:20,901
That's my way
of saying thank you

109
00:04:20,968 --> 00:04:21,934
For the last time
i saw you.

110
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:23,567
Well, nice to see you,
too.

111
00:04:23,634 --> 00:04:25,767
Although i thought
you'd still be running

112
00:04:25,834 --> 00:04:27,501
From those angry
south americans.

113
00:04:27,567 --> 00:04:29,133
You know, i would be,

114
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:33,133
But it seems that a rival cartel
got an anonymous shipment

115
00:04:33,200 --> 00:04:35,534
Of ak-47s
and rocket launchers,

116
00:04:35,601 --> 00:04:38,701
So those angry south americans
were a little busy,

117
00:04:38,767 --> 00:04:41,133
What with
all the killing and dying.

118
00:04:41,200 --> 00:04:43,033
You financed a private war so
you could get back to miami?

119
00:04:43,100 --> 00:04:44,300
Why?

120
00:04:44,367 --> 00:04:46,334
An exciting
business opportunity.

121
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:48,200
A limo company.

122
00:04:48,267 --> 00:04:50,901
Actually, i think
you might know the owner.

123
00:04:50,968 --> 00:04:52,267
Nate.

124
00:04:52,334 --> 00:04:53,534
You're nate's investor.

125
00:04:53,601 --> 00:04:55,467
But not just me.
i have a partner.

126
00:04:55,534 --> 00:04:56,868
Nate's with him now.

127
00:04:56,934 --> 00:05:00,000
Doesn't nate look happy?
closing his little deal.

128
00:05:00,067 --> 00:05:01,934
Of course, he doesn't realize
that his investor

129
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:04,300
Is actually an enforcer from
sicily called "the butcher."

130
00:05:04,367 --> 00:05:05,567
Brought him over special
just for this.

131
00:05:05,634 --> 00:05:07,400
Brennen, if you --

132
00:05:07,467 --> 00:05:10,601
Oh, oh, oh, michael, no.
it's not up to me.

133
00:05:10,667 --> 00:05:14,234
Whether nate's meeting ends
in a bullet or a handshake

134
00:05:14,300 --> 00:05:15,868
Is entirely up to you.

135
00:05:15,934 --> 00:05:18,367
See, you're gonna be running
some errands for me today.

136
00:05:18,434 --> 00:05:22,934
Just think of me as, uh...
your new boss.

137
00:05:35,601 --> 00:05:38,767
Cellphone, keys, wallet,
and your sunglasses.

138
00:05:38,834 --> 00:05:40,234
I want to see
those pretty eyes.

139
00:05:42,701 --> 00:05:43,834
Let's go.

140
00:05:43,901 --> 00:05:45,734
You're certainly
in a hurry.

141
00:05:45,801 --> 00:05:48,701
Is this little job of yours
time-sensitive?

142
00:05:48,767 --> 00:05:49,901
Listen to you.

143
00:05:49,968 --> 00:05:52,434
Probing for intel
from the get-go.

144
00:05:52,501 --> 00:05:53,667
You are a sly one,
aren't you?

145
00:05:53,734 --> 00:05:55,267
You know,
you could save me some time.

146
00:05:55,334 --> 00:05:56,367
You could tell me
what we're doing.

147
00:05:56,434 --> 00:05:57,467
Hmm.
uh, pass.

148
00:05:57,534 --> 00:05:59,000
You're just a key,
michael.

149
00:05:59,067 --> 00:06:02,100
Keys don't need to know what's
behind the doors they unlock.

150
00:06:02,167 --> 00:06:05,133
Now, rules for the superspy.
i give orders, you obey.

151
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:06,934
You try to escape,
nate dies.

152
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:09,334
Fail to complete a task,
nate dies.

153
00:06:09,400 --> 00:06:10,634
Refuse an order --

154
00:06:10,701 --> 00:06:12,133
I get it.

155
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:13,801
But i'm not playing fetch
until i know nate's okay.

156
00:06:13,868 --> 00:06:16,601
Michael, we covered this.
the picture?

157
00:06:16,667 --> 00:06:18,434
No, that could have been taken
hours ago.

158
00:06:18,501 --> 00:06:20,501
Prove nate's alive now,
or your project ends here.

159
00:06:20,567 --> 00:06:21,868
Well, how about this?

160
00:06:21,934 --> 00:06:24,567
<i>you stop making demands,
or your life ends here.</i>

161
00:06:24,634 --> 00:06:26,667
<i>your first priority
when you're captured</i>

162
00:06:26,734 --> 00:06:29,434
<i>is to make it clear that
your cooperation isn't free.</i>

163
00:06:29,501 --> 00:06:32,567
<i>your captor gets what he wants
if you get what you want.</i>

164
00:06:32,634 --> 00:06:33,601
Get in the car.

165
00:06:33,667 --> 00:06:35,100
You're the one stopping me.

166
00:06:35,167 --> 00:06:37,067
Prove to me
i'm not wasting my time.

167
00:06:37,133 --> 00:06:40,400
<i>in any healthy relationship,</i>

168
00:06:40,467 --> 00:06:42,100
<i>there needs to be
some give and take.</i>

169
00:06:42,167 --> 00:06:43,200
One word...

170
00:06:43,267 --> 00:06:44,334
And nate dies.

171
00:06:44,400 --> 00:06:46,300
Not right away, of course.

172
00:06:46,367 --> 00:06:49,200
My partner is a man
who really enjoys his work.

173
00:06:49,267 --> 00:06:52,367
[ cellphone rings ]

174
00:06:52,434 --> 00:06:53,434
Yeah, it's me.

175
00:06:53,501 --> 00:06:55,400
Put our friend on.

176
00:06:55,467 --> 00:06:56,467
It's for you.

177
00:06:58,334 --> 00:06:59,367
This is nate.

178
00:06:59,434 --> 00:07:00,567
Nate westen,
simon davis.

179
00:07:00,634 --> 00:07:02,267
Simon, my man.
hey, you heading over?

180
00:07:02,334 --> 00:07:03,934
Uh, i've got
a few errands to run,

181
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:06,334
But you can work out the broad
strokes with my partner.

182
00:07:06,400 --> 00:07:07,667
Be careful, though, buddy,

183
00:07:07,734 --> 00:07:09,801
He can be ruthless once
he starts to work you over.

184
00:07:09,868 --> 00:07:12,801
Yeah, no, i'm looking forward
to the challenge.

185
00:07:12,868 --> 00:07:14,334
Good, buddy.
i'll see you soon.

186
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:15,467
All right.

187
00:07:15,534 --> 00:07:16,801
Happy?
now, get in the damn car.

188
00:07:22,667 --> 00:07:24,334
So, this is the house

189
00:07:24,400 --> 00:07:27,234
<i>where the michael westen
grew up, huh?</i>

190
00:07:27,300 --> 00:07:30,234
And now you're living here.
with his mom?

191
00:07:30,300 --> 00:07:31,667
I'm just crashing here
for a while, okay?

192
00:07:31,734 --> 00:07:33,133
I'm just helping out
with some home repairs.

193
00:07:33,200 --> 00:07:34,133
It's not like that.

194
00:07:35,567 --> 00:07:37,367
You got here fast, barry.
oh, yeah, yeah.

195
00:07:37,434 --> 00:07:38,901
My salon's
in the neighborhood, so...

196
00:07:38,968 --> 00:07:40,968
Anyway, so michael's
got a cop problem?

197
00:07:41,033 --> 00:07:43,467
Yeah, it's making life
unpleasant for all of us.

198
00:07:43,534 --> 00:07:45,067
We need a little help
to make it go away.

199
00:07:45,133 --> 00:07:47,167
Okay.
well, tiny issue, all right?

200
00:07:47,234 --> 00:07:49,367
My life coach
has strongly suggested

201
00:07:49,434 --> 00:07:51,901
That i try and avoid
stressful situations.

202
00:07:51,968 --> 00:07:54,167
Barry, we're not asking you
to storm the station.

203
00:07:54,234 --> 00:07:56,133
Just open a joint bank account
with mike...

204
00:07:56,200 --> 00:07:58,801
And a mayor's aide.

205
00:07:58,868 --> 00:08:00,234
[ sighs ]

206
00:08:00,300 --> 00:08:01,834
Great.

207
00:08:01,901 --> 00:08:03,300
Why don't we just throw a judge
in there while we're at it?

208
00:08:03,367 --> 00:08:04,501
Barry, we called you

209
00:08:04,567 --> 00:08:05,868
Because this cop
isn't just our problem.

210
00:08:05,934 --> 00:08:07,901
She's interrogating everybody
in mike's life.

211
00:08:07,968 --> 00:08:10,133
You really want to find out
what questions she has

212
00:08:10,200 --> 00:08:11,934
For his dear old
money-laundering pal barry?

213
00:08:14,567 --> 00:08:16,934
Here's what you're gonna do.

214
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:19,067
Go here and tell fabian

215
00:08:19,133 --> 00:08:22,634
That i'm giving you
the portable skimmer.

216
00:08:22,701 --> 00:08:24,934
Fabian?

217
00:08:25,033 --> 00:08:26,467
I hired an intern.

218
00:08:27,667 --> 00:08:30,000
Once your pretty little hands
swipe that card...

219
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:33,801
...my pretty little hands are
gonna do some financial magic.

220
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:36,801
Yeah, uh, say, barry,

221
00:08:36,868 --> 00:08:38,467
Before you and your hands
get too busy,

222
00:08:38,534 --> 00:08:40,033
I thought maybe you could
help me out

223
00:08:40,100 --> 00:08:41,501
With a little
home-improvement project.

224
00:08:44,501 --> 00:08:45,868
So who's the guy
with the purse?

225
00:08:45,934 --> 00:08:47,734
That's barry.

226
00:08:47,801 --> 00:08:49,801
What does he do?

227
00:08:49,868 --> 00:08:53,567
He's sam's
financial consultant.

228
00:08:55,634 --> 00:08:58,467
Now you got to hold it up.
hold it in position.

229
00:08:58,534 --> 00:09:01,000
I got to put this thing up.
hold that down.

230
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:10,067
We're here.
where's "here"?

231
00:09:10,133 --> 00:09:11,300
You see that building?

232
00:09:11,367 --> 00:09:14,000
There's a hardware key
in a desk in office 237.

233
00:09:14,067 --> 00:09:16,834
In about a half an hour,
it's gonna be in my pocket.

234
00:09:19,167 --> 00:09:20,901
This gets you
past security.

235
00:09:20,968 --> 00:09:22,267
Besides the guards,

236
00:09:22,334 --> 00:09:24,434
There should be nobody
in the building on a sunday.

237
00:09:24,501 --> 00:09:25,901
I hope you know
more about the building

238
00:09:25,968 --> 00:09:27,300
Than my jacket size.

239
00:09:27,367 --> 00:09:29,767
Superspy, you got bigger things
to worry about

240
00:09:29,834 --> 00:09:31,067
Than how pretty you
look in your coat.

241
00:09:31,133 --> 00:09:33,300
The offices are wired
to the building's alarms.

242
00:09:33,367 --> 00:09:35,033
You ready?

243
00:09:35,100 --> 00:09:36,133
How long do i have inside?

244
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:40,334
If you're not going to tell me
what we're doing here --

245
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:43,968
Westen,
just eat what's on your plate.

246
00:09:45,434 --> 00:09:46,801
One more thing.

247
