744
00:32:19,433 --> 00:32:22,634
Well, it's more like a russian
nesting doll than a company.

745
00:32:22,700 --> 00:32:24,934
You know, i dug through
nine subsidiaries

746
00:32:25,001 --> 00:32:26,334
In six countries.

747
00:32:26,400 --> 00:32:29,001
All i got was
"belle anna holding"
out of zurich.

748
00:32:29,067 --> 00:32:31,567
He sends 40k every 6 months,
it looks like.

749
00:32:31,634 --> 00:32:33,167
A lot of work to hide
80 grand a year.

750
00:32:33,234 --> 00:32:34,800
Yeah, no kidding.

751
00:32:34,867 --> 00:32:36,400
There's no business records,
either, for belle anna.

752
00:32:36,467 --> 00:32:39,268
Mike, that's it.
that's all there is.

753
00:32:39,334 --> 00:32:40,301
Mike, you still there?

754
00:32:49,101 --> 00:32:50,600
He had a tie clip.

755
00:32:50,667 --> 00:32:51,901
Looked like a gift.

756
00:32:51,967 --> 00:32:54,201
Didn't want to talk
about his family.

757
00:32:54,268 --> 00:32:58,001
Belle anna holding?
i think i might know what it is.

758
00:32:58,067 --> 00:32:59,201
You think or you know?

759
00:32:59,268 --> 00:33:02,167
Somewhere in between.
does fi have any c-4?

760
00:33:02,234 --> 00:33:03,967
Well, it's fi, mike.
you got to ask?

761
00:33:04,034 --> 00:33:06,600
Can you walk barry
through intercepting
a call in 10 minutes?

762
00:33:06,667 --> 00:33:08,901
That's gonna be tight,
but, yeah, sure.

763
00:33:08,967 --> 00:33:11,301
Sounds like you've got
something good, mike.

764
00:33:12,667 --> 00:33:14,600
[ cellphone beeps ]

765
00:33:34,167 --> 00:33:36,400
This is just outside
of my comfort zone, okay?

766
00:33:36,467 --> 00:33:39,201
I'm just saying, i'm not that
great with british dialects!

767
00:33:39,268 --> 00:33:41,967
There's no other way, barry.
mike's counting on you.

768
00:33:42,034 --> 00:33:43,067
Ugh. i --

769
00:33:43,134 --> 00:33:44,700
Just breathe, barry.

770
00:33:44,767 --> 00:33:45,867
It'll all be fine.

771
00:33:45,934 --> 00:33:46,800
Yeah, yeah, okay.

772
00:33:49,334 --> 00:33:50,901
How big do we want this?

773
00:33:50,967 --> 00:33:52,234
Well,
enough to make a point.

774
00:33:53,268 --> 00:33:54,234
But not kill the neighbors.

775
00:33:54,301 --> 00:33:56,667
Really?

776
00:33:58,268 --> 00:33:59,834
Should be good, then.

777
00:34:02,800 --> 00:34:05,767
Tell me this is a joke.

778
00:34:05,834 --> 00:34:07,800
Was i unclear
about the situation here?

779
00:34:07,867 --> 00:34:09,934
No, you were very clear.

780
00:34:10,001 --> 00:34:12,368
I had the box in my hands,
then i decided you never will.

781
00:34:12,433 --> 00:34:13,400
Ever.

782
00:34:15,034 --> 00:34:16,400
[ remote beeps ]

783
00:34:18,467 --> 00:34:19,533
Jesus, fi!

784
00:34:19,600 --> 00:34:21,467
I told you
not to kill the neighbors!

785
00:34:21,533 --> 00:34:23,767
You told me to make a point.
take your picture.

786
00:34:23,834 --> 00:34:24,700
Ugh.

787
00:34:25,834 --> 00:34:27,368
[ cellphone beeps ]
we should go.

788
00:34:33,700 --> 00:34:34,867
Get it now.

789
00:34:34,934 --> 00:34:37,533
Oh, god, please don't.

790
00:34:37,600 --> 00:34:39,500
I-i'm through playing games,
westen.

791
00:34:39,567 --> 00:34:40,734
[ cellphone beeps ]

792
00:34:40,800 --> 00:34:42,034
I think you got
a text message.

793
00:34:42,101 --> 00:34:43,700
It can wait.

794
00:34:43,767 --> 00:34:44,767
No, it can't.

795
00:34:51,201 --> 00:34:53,234
What the hell is this?

796
00:34:53,301 --> 00:34:55,101
It's your house,
i believe.

797
00:34:55,167 --> 00:34:57,034
You did this?

798
00:34:57,101 --> 00:34:59,400
You found my place in miami
and blew it up?

799
00:34:59,467 --> 00:35:00,567
Okay.

800
00:35:00,634 --> 00:35:02,567
If that's all you've got...

801
00:35:02,634 --> 00:35:04,167
Oh, that's not all.

802
00:35:04,234 --> 00:35:08,301
Since we last met, i became
an expert on tyler brennen.

803
00:35:08,368 --> 00:35:10,001
I know everything about
you, from where you get
your teeth cleaned

804
00:35:10,067 --> 00:35:11,600
To where
you do your banking.

805
00:35:11,667 --> 00:35:13,567
<i>did your banking.
i drained the accounts.</i>

806
00:35:13,634 --> 00:35:14,734
[ laughs ]

807
00:35:14,800 --> 00:35:17,034
Wow.
that is a desperate bluff.

808
00:35:17,101 --> 00:35:18,867
"a" for effort, but --

809
00:35:18,934 --> 00:35:20,767
I probably wouldn't
believe me, either.

810
00:35:20,834 --> 00:35:22,967
Hamstead bank and trust
has some fine security.

811
00:35:23,034 --> 00:35:25,101
But if you want to make
a quick phone call,

812
00:35:25,167 --> 00:35:26,767
Put your mind at ease,
i'll wait.

813
00:35:26,834 --> 00:35:30,001
[ cellphone beeps,
rings ]

814
00:35:34,967 --> 00:35:36,533
[ exhales deeply ]

815
00:35:36,600 --> 00:35:38,334
[ british accent ]
hamstead.

816
00:35:38,400 --> 00:35:39,867
Are you currently banking
with us?

817
00:35:39,934 --> 00:35:41,500
Yes, i need
to check my balance.

818
00:35:41,567 --> 00:35:46,201
Account number 06101966,

819
00:35:46,268 --> 00:35:47,867
Pin 1208.

820
00:35:47,934 --> 00:35:49,034
1208.

821
00:35:49,101 --> 00:35:50,167
One moment.

822
00:35:50,234 --> 00:35:51,467
Mr. brennen.

823
00:35:51,533 --> 00:35:53,800
Are you calling about
this morning's transfer?

824
00:35:53,867 --> 00:35:54,967
Transfer?

825
00:35:55,034 --> 00:35:56,800
Yes,
at 11:00 a.m. local time,

826
00:35:56,867 --> 00:36:01,400
261,000 was transferred
out of this account.

827
00:36:01,467 --> 00:36:05,600
Your current balance is 4.
if you like --

828
00:36:05,667 --> 00:36:07,234
No.

829
00:36:07,301 --> 00:36:10,600
<i>you're not this good.
nobody is this good.</i>

830
00:36:10,667 --> 00:36:11,800
Yes, i am.

831
00:36:11,867 --> 00:36:13,201
I am so good, in fact,

832
00:36:13,268 --> 00:36:16,667
That i can put it all back,
right now, if you let us go.

833
00:36:18,400 --> 00:36:21,567
You know what?
i don't care.

834
00:36:21,634 --> 00:36:23,101
Just stuff.

835
00:36:23,167 --> 00:36:27,268
Burn it all down.
i can start over.

836
00:36:27,334 --> 00:36:29,167
But you and your brother
are finished.

837
00:36:33,368 --> 00:36:35,567
What about belle anna?

838
00:36:37,467 --> 00:36:40,001
I mean, annabelle?

839
00:36:40,067 --> 00:36:41,467
Annabelle?

840
00:36:41,533 --> 00:36:42,533
Annabelle.

841
00:36:42,600 --> 00:36:43,901
Your daughter.

842
00:36:43,967 --> 00:36:46,734
The one who gave you
that nifty tie pin,

843
00:36:46,800 --> 00:36:49,834
The one you're sending
to private school in switzerland

844
00:36:49,901 --> 00:36:52,400
For $40,000 a semester.
you son of a bitch.

845
00:36:52,467 --> 00:36:54,934
[ cellphone dialing ]

846
00:36:55,001 --> 00:36:56,167
[ ringing ]

847
00:36:57,400 --> 00:36:59,101
Annabelle: hello?

848
00:36:59,167 --> 00:37:02,634
Sweetie, it's daddy.
are -- are you okay?

849
00:37:02,700 --> 00:37:06,067
Daddy? yeah.
why are you calling so late?

850
00:37:06,134 --> 00:37:08,001
Honey, i-i'm sorry.

851
00:37:08,067 --> 00:37:12,167
I forgot, uh...
i forgot what time it was.

852
00:37:12,234 --> 00:37:14,400
You -- you go back to sleep,
okay, pumpkin?

853
00:37:14,467 --> 00:37:16,201
I'll call you tomorrow.

854
00:37:17,767 --> 00:37:20,101
This isn't you, westen.

855
00:37:20,167 --> 00:37:22,467
You're capable of a lot,
but you wouldn't hurt a child.

856
00:37:22,533 --> 00:37:24,533
But you would, brennen.

857
00:37:24,600 --> 00:37:26,134
<i>this is your game.</i>

858
00:37:26,201 --> 00:37:27,400
<i>we're playing by your rules.</i>

859
00:37:27,467 --> 00:37:29,234
Why go through all this?
why not just --

860
00:37:29,301 --> 00:37:31,467
Took some time to get
an assassin into place

861
00:37:31,533 --> 00:37:32,734
Halfway around the world.

862
00:37:32,800 --> 00:37:33,867
You're lying.

863
00:37:33,934 --> 00:37:35,700
You want to find out?
shoot me.

864
00:37:38,400 --> 00:37:42,800
If you go near her,
if you touch her, if --

865
00:37:42,867 --> 00:37:47,901
If she so much as skins her knee
on the playground,

866
00:37:47,967 --> 00:37:50,400
I swear to god, westen,

867
00:37:50,467 --> 00:37:53,567
I will spend the rest of my life
destroying you...

868
00:37:55,533 --> 00:37:58,500
...and everything you love.

869
00:37:58,567 --> 00:38:00,467
Of course you will,
brennen.

870
00:38:00,533 --> 00:38:01,667
She's your family.

871
00:38:05,001 --> 00:38:07,767
[ vehicle door opens ]

872
00:38:13,400 --> 00:38:16,368
You'll hear from me again,
michael.

873
00:38:16,433 --> 00:38:18,834
Yeah, you owe me
a christmas card.

874
00:38:21,700 --> 00:38:24,500
[ engines turns over ]

875
00:38:24,567 --> 00:38:26,767
[ groans ]

876
00:38:26,834 --> 00:38:29,167
[ tires screeching ]

877
00:38:39,968 --> 00:38:41,834
Hey, nate.

878
00:38:41,901 --> 00:38:44,367
How's the arm?

879
00:38:44,434 --> 00:38:47,334
Um, it's okay.
it's a little bit sore.

880
00:38:49,667 --> 00:38:50,968
What'd you tell mom?

881
00:38:51,034 --> 00:38:52,901
I told her i was attacked
by a mugger.

882
00:38:54,400 --> 00:38:57,068
I didn't want her
to get scared.

883
00:38:57,133 --> 00:38:59,133
You thinking about
sticking around for a while?

884
00:38:59,200 --> 00:39:00,267
I don't know.

885
00:39:00,334 --> 00:39:02,634
Feels a little weird
being back now.

886
00:39:02,701 --> 00:39:06,068
You know, i thought i was here
to land this big deal, and...

887
00:39:06,133 --> 00:39:07,400
And instead...

888
00:39:07,467 --> 00:39:09,300
You were being used
by a sociopath to get to me?

889
00:39:09,367 --> 00:39:11,801
Yeah.

890
00:39:11,867 --> 00:39:16,434
You know, i really thought
i had something this time.

891
00:39:16,500 --> 00:39:20,200
Nate, i know it's hard sometimes
being my brother.

892
00:39:20,267 --> 00:39:21,500
It's okay, bro.

893
00:39:21,567 --> 00:39:22,534
I'm getting used to it.

894
00:39:25,233 --> 00:39:27,133
Michael.
i didn't hear you come in.

895
00:39:27,200 --> 00:39:28,500
Here, honey, drink this.

896
00:39:28,567 --> 00:39:29,834
Hey, mom.

897
00:39:29,901 --> 00:39:31,734
I just came by to see
how nate was feeling,

898
00:39:31,801 --> 00:39:33,200
You know,
after his mugging.

899
00:39:33,267 --> 00:39:34,801
Yes.

900
00:39:34,867 --> 00:39:37,634
You know, michael,
it seems like --

901
00:39:37,701 --> 00:39:40,500
I don't know,
such a big coincidence

902
00:39:40,567 --> 00:39:45,300
That sam, fi, and barry
were all mysteriously busy

903
00:39:45,367 --> 00:39:47,300
At the exact same time

904
00:39:47,367 --> 00:39:49,200
That nate was being beaten up
by his mugger.

905
00:39:49,267 --> 00:39:50,334
[ chuckles ]

906
00:39:50,400 --> 00:39:52,300
Well,
maybe it's because...

907
00:39:52,367 --> 00:39:53,567
Michael, please.

908
00:39:53,634 --> 00:39:56,300
I'd rather you not lie
right to my face.

909
00:39:56,367 --> 00:39:58,634
I'm just glad
both of my boys are home.

910
00:39:58,701 --> 00:40:00,334
And that
i got to know barry.

911
00:40:00,400 --> 00:40:01,701
He's coming over later

912
00:40:01,767 --> 00:40:04,233
With some new
eucalyptus-infused hair gel.

913
00:40:04,300 --> 00:40:05,968
We're gonna have
a product party.

914
00:40:12,734 --> 00:40:14,367
How's nate doing?

915
00:40:14,434 --> 00:40:15,467
Healing.

916
00:40:15,534 --> 00:40:18,734
You know,
i'm starting to think...

917
00:40:18,801 --> 00:40:22,300
I screw up his life
better than he does.

918
00:40:22,367 --> 00:40:23,968
Oh, don't be so hard
on yourself.

919
00:40:24,034 --> 00:40:26,100
He wouldn't be breathing
if it weren't for you.

920
00:40:26,167 --> 00:40:27,734
I had a little help.

921
00:40:29,233 --> 00:40:30,200
Thanks, fi.

922
00:40:30,267 --> 00:40:33,367
Hey.
he's family.

923
00:40:33,434 --> 00:40:34,801
[ knock on door ]

924
00:40:35,734 --> 00:40:37,701
Expecting someone?

925
00:40:40,434 --> 00:40:41,701
Paxson:
mr. westen.

926
00:40:41,767 --> 00:40:42,834
May i have a word?

927
00:40:42,901 --> 00:40:47,200
Detective, you look unhappy.
come on in.

928
00:40:47,267 --> 00:40:49,701
Is your friend coming?

929
00:40:49,767 --> 00:40:51,001
Oh, detective lopez?

930
00:40:51,068 --> 00:40:52,467
No.
he's been suspended.

931
00:40:52,534 --> 00:40:54,434
Ooh, has he been naughty?

932
00:40:54,500 --> 00:40:56,267
He's been doing his job,
actually.

933
00:40:56,334 --> 00:40:58,367
He grilled a mayor's aide
for three hours

934
00:40:58,434 --> 00:41:00,534
About some mysterious
bank account she opened

935
00:41:00,601 --> 00:41:02,034
With a michael westen.

936
00:41:02,100 --> 00:41:03,767
Turned out
to be a bank error,

937
00:41:03,834 --> 00:41:05,634
But not before the mayor
got upset enough

938
00:41:05,701 --> 00:41:06,801
To have his badge yanked.

939
00:41:06,867 --> 00:41:08,200
That's too bad.

940
00:41:08,267 --> 00:41:10,001
I assume you were trying
to get to me.

941
00:41:10,068 --> 00:41:11,434
You'll be glad to know

942
00:41:11,500 --> 00:41:13,500
I didn't come by
to ask you questions this time.

943
00:41:13,567 --> 00:41:15,601
I came by to say this --

944
00:41:15,667 --> 00:41:19,767
You want to play rough,
i can give as good as i get.

